<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">
$IF($V(IQEYE6),<!--,)
<br>
"Digital Pan Tilt Zoom" allows the viewer to pan about the
      displayed image.  The controls are in the title bar.
<br>
<br>
With the mouse pointer, click on any point in the image to 
recenter the image around that point.  

<br>
<br>
    Click on the arrow buttons to move the center of
      view half a frame in the desired direction.
<br>
<br>
    Click on the zoom "+" button to zoom in.
<br>
<br>
    Click on the zoom "-" button to zoom out.
<br>
$IF($V(IQEYE6),-->,)
<br>
    Click on the size "+" button to increase the size of the viewed image.
<br>
<br>
    Click on the size "-" button to decrease the size of the viewed image.
<br>
<br>
    Click on the 'max size' button to view a full sized image.
<br>
<br>
    Click on the stop button to view a single frame instead of an image stream.

<br><br>
If there is a "MULTI VIEW" button, click on it to bring up the 
the multi view page, which displays images from up to 9 cameras at once. 

</font>

